ce:section.ce:para:
Differential scanning calorimetry (DSC) analysis is realized to determine the glass transition temperatures (T

                              g
                           ) of Dy3+-doped tellurite and silicate glasses in a Netzsch DSC 204F1 (limit of detection:<0.1 μV, with an error estimate of± 1 °C) instrument. DSC analysis is performed with a constant sample weight of 25 ± 1 mg in aluminum pans under 25 mL/min flowing argon gas atmosphere with a heating rate of 10 °C/min. The amorphous nature of synthesized glasses is checked by X-ray diffraction (XRD) analysis in a Philips/PANalytical X′pert Pro XRD instrument using CuKα radiation at 45 kV and 40 mA with a step size of 0.02° in the 2θ range from 20°− 80°.
